{{- comment -}}
  snippets/header-cart.liquid
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ROW 3d: Cart icon + live item-count badge.

  VARIABLES PASSED IN: none.

  GLOBALS READ DIRECTLY:
    cart.item_count   — total number of items currently in the cart.
                        Shopify keeps this in sync on every page load.
    routes.cart_url   — resolves to /cart.

  CALLER (sections/header.liquid):
    {% render 'header-cart' %}

  BADGE BEHAVIOUR:
    - Visible only when cart.item_count > 0 (no empty red circle).
    - aria-label on the <a> reads the count aloud for screen readers,
      e.g. "Cart, 3 items".

  STEP 3 NOTE:
    When you add an Ajax cart drawer, attach the open event to
    [data-cart-trigger] rather than following the href. The badge count
    can then be updated via a targeted innerHTML swap on .header__cart-badge
    after each add-to-cart response — no full page reload needed.
    The [data-cart-count] attribute on the badge span is the update target.
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{{- endcomment -}}

<a
  href="{{ routes.cart_url }}"
  class="header__cart"
  aria-label="Cart, {{ cart.item_count }} {{ cart.item_count | pluralize: 'item', 'items' }}"
  data-cart-trigger
>
  <span class="header__cart-icon-wrap" aria-hidden="true">
    🛍️
    {%- if cart.item_count > 0 -%}
      <span class="header__cart-badge" data-cart-count>
        {{- cart.item_count -}}
      </span>
    {%- endif -%}
  </span>
  <span class="header__cart-label">Cart</span>
</a>
